<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/talking_point/2236871.stm">BBC News</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
Basically, the first Republican Lord Mayor of Belfast has put the tricolour up as well as the union jack, and it has outraged people. Firstly I shall demonstrate why some people dislike the obvious English readers:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> It's a disgrace that this flag should be allowed to fly over Belfast City Hall. Belfast is a part of the United Kingdom and should fly the flag of this country and not the flag of a foreign, terrorist supporting country. <br>
Stewart, Great Britain <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Ahum, if they where to read the story they would find out it was in the lord mayors study, and the chance of the Irish flag flying outside over City Hall is currently small, until there is a vote. That kind of thing wouldn't cuase outrage, it would cause death. Ireland is not a terrorist country, and the IRA have never been stated as terrorists. They are freedom fighters, and maybe she he/she has missed out the news over the last 8 years!<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Belfast should have its own flag and identity portraying its roots as Ireland. Maybe the tricolour with the union jack in the corner? <br>
Dave, England <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I like the idea yet it's unlikely. People want to be one or the other, and I like for it to be like wouldn't work. Unlike Australia its not a colony. The British and Irish governments have been in many talks about joint-ownership, yet it's not possible as people have to be one or the other. There was even something on the news about fights over whether cows where counted as Irish or British, but I don't know the details.<br>
<br>
There is a flag for Ulster, yet I am unsure if there is a flag for Northern Ireland.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>
No way should the Irish flag be allowed in the Belfast City Hall. It is not part of the Republic of Ireland but part of UK. This is just another attempt to cause trouble. It is about time Tony Blair stood up for the rights of the people in Belfast and stop giving in to Sinn Fein! <br>
Paula, Netherlands <br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Now they are right, it is part of the UK. I can't tell you the actual figures, but I would say 53% unionist. The future shows a clear catholic majority of the north. The south has a 3% protestant minority. There are talks about a border poll (deciding the future) in May 2003 along with the general elections. Both sides want this, as they both believe it will show a clear majority vote for there side. Also, the Unionists think it will get a huge number going out to vote, which they think will be good for them. British law states that when there is one border poll, another must follow every 7 years, so that means another one in 2010. This basically means Ireland will one day be united if the future Catholic majority theory is true.<br>
<br>
God, I have went on too much. Tell me your thoughts on what we should have as a flag, and what you think about the Lord Mayor putting the Irish Tricolour up in his personal study (the rest of the city hall is literally covered in union jacks if you look inside, so he wants to feel at home, as well as the old equality issue).<br>
<br>
Oh, I will also add that the Irish Tricolour was made whenever ROI seperated from the UK as far as I know. Before that Ireland would use another flag I think, probably with the harp angel thing on it (i really have no idea to be honesT!). The green of the flag represents the nationalists while the orange represents union (orange men etc.) and the white is meant to show how they should live in peace. Many people now see it as something far from that of course.<br>
<br>
Give me your feedback! I dare you.. <p></p><span class=m><i></i></span><hr size=1>   &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fbbardenfrm57.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=33.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/reply.gif border=0 width=20 height=20 alt="reply to this message" align=absmiddle></a>   <br><br></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCE6FF><td colspan=2><table cellpadding=8 cellspacing=0 width=100%><tr><td nowrap width=20% valign=top><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub103.ezboard.com/us4turn3.showPublicProfile?language=EN>S4TuRn3</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://digilander.iol.it/gar1/icon/fantasia/stripe.gif" BORDER=0> </span><br><BR><img src=http://www.syntax-web.net/img/satel.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60><br> <span class=usertitle>On another planet<br /><img src='http://www.bbarden.com/img/levels/userlevel-mod.gif' /></span><br>  ezSupporter<br></td><td valign=top align=left class=m width=80%><span class=m><font color=#FF0000>Posted: 9/9/02 6:27:02 pm</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br><span class=title> Re: Flags Issue</span><hr size=1> I'm not very concerned, so I can't say anything... in fact I don't really care whether the Ulster is linked to the Eire or to the United Kingdom... only people living there can have that opinion, can't they ? <p></p><span class=m><i></i></span><hr size=1>   &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fbbardenfrm57.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=33.topic&index=1><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/reply.gif border=0 width=20 height=20 alt="reply to this message" align=absmiddle></a>   <br><br></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td colspan=2><table cellpadding=8 cellspacing=0 width=100%><tr><td nowrap width=20% valign=top><span clas