<br>
I don't know about it being a successful part of the UK, but I don't think people realise it is part of Ireland, and I think it's the idea of a foreign army on an island...as for Wales, its controlled pretty much by London....Edinburgh is doing better for itself, yet Glasgow is the true Scottish capital anyone smartass will know.(I know it).. <p></p><span class=m><i></i></span><hr size=1>   &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fbbardenfrm57.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=33.topic&index=3><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/reply.gif border=0 width=20 height=20 alt="reply to this message" align=absmiddle></a>   <br><br></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td colspan=2><table cellpadding=8 cellspacing=0 width=100%><tr><td nowrap width=20% valign=top><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub103.ezboard.com/ubrenfitz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BrenFitz</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.unique-hardware.co.uk/server-smilies/cwm/alien/coolmad.gif" BORDER=0> </span><br><BR><img src=http://home.datacomm.ch/m2karchives/realm.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60><br> <span class=usertitle>KFC Monster<br /><img src=http://www.bbarden.com/img/levels/userlevel-mod.gif /></span><br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m width=80%><span class=m><font color=#FF0000>Posted: 9/10/02 9:56:22 pm</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br><span class=title> Re: Flags Issue</span><hr size=1> Outside the Liverpool town Hall they fly both the Union Jack and St. George's Cross<br>
